videos.description: Connecticut's Kia Nurse steals and dishes it out to an open Kate Lou Samuelson who drills a 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Samuelson drains a 3

videos.description: Connecticut's Gabby Williams steals and takes it to the other end of the court for an open layup.
videos.headline: Williams steals and scores for Huskies

videos.description: The Huskies' Crystal Dangerfield drives to the basket uncontested for a layup.
videos.headline: UConn's Dangerfield finds open lane for layup

videos.description: The Huskies' Katie Lou Samuelson doesn't hesitate and drains a 3-pointer while guarded by Louisville's Sam Fuehring.
videos.headline: UConn's Samuelson drills contested 3

videos.description: The Huskies' Gabby Williams kicks it out to a wide-open Kia Nurse who makes the easy layup in the final seconds of the game against Louisville.
videos.headline: UConn's Nurse makes dagger layup

videos.description: UConn's Kia Nurse breaks down how her team held off Louisville in the third and fourth quarter in the Huskies 69-58 victory over the Cardinals.
videos.headline: Nurse: 'We did a good job with stops and scores'

videos.description: UConn's associate head coach Chris Dailey describes what it means to be a 2018 Women's Basketball Hall of Fame inductee.
videos.headline: Dailey: 'I just feel fortunate'
